## nyne — Filesystem Guide

> This directory is a **nyne** FUSE mount over `{{ source_dir }}`.
> Languages: {{ languages }}

**Prefer the Read tool** for reading virtual files. Use Bash (`cat`, `echo >`, `sed -i`) for batch reads (brace expansion), writes, and shell pipelines.
All `@`-namespaced entries are real files — Read tool, Edit tool, and Bash all work on them.

### Quick Start

```sh
# 1. Read the file-level overview (symbol table, metadata)
cat file.{{ ext }}@/OVERVIEW.md

# 2. Read the symbols directory overview
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md

# 3. Read a specific symbol's body
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/my_function.{{ ext }}

# 4. Read a symbol's full definition (same as above, explicit form)
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/my_function@/body.{{ ext }}

# 5. Edit a symbol (write new body content)
echo 'new content' > file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/my_function@/body.{{ ext }}

# 6. Read/edit the import block
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}

# 7. Read specific lines (escape hatch — prefer symbol-targeted reads)
cat file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20
```

### File Structure

Every recognized source file gains an `@/` companion namespace:

```
file.{{ ext }}@/OVERVIEW.md                    # file-level overview (metadata + symbol table)
file.{{ ext }}@/DIAGNOSTICS.md                 # compiler errors/warnings
file.{{ ext }}@/lines                          # all lines (read, write, append)
file.{{ ext }}@/lines:M-N                      # line range (read, write, rm deletes range)
file.{{ ext }}@/rename/                         # file rename preview diffs (import updates)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md            # symbol table with line ranges and signatures
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}              # import block (read, write, append)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo.{{ ext }}                  # shorthand for Foo@/body.{{ ext }}
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}            # full definition (read, write, append)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/signature.{{ ext }}       # declaration line (read, write)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/docstring.txt     # docstring (read, write, append, truncate)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/decorators.{{ ext }}      # decorators (read, write, truncate)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/CALLERS.md        # incoming call sites (symlinked to caller symbols)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DEPS.md           # outgoing dependencies (symlinked to callee symbols)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/REFERENCES.md     # all usage sites (symlinked to referencing symbols)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/          # LSP code actions as .diff files
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/rename/           # LSP rename preview diffs (lookup-only)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/             # batch edit staging area
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/OVERVIEW.md       # child symbol listing
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/            # type-filtered symlinks
```

**Git companion files (file-level):**

```
file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md                   # per-line authorship
file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md                     # commit log for this file
file.{{ ext }}@/git/CONTRIBUTORS.md            # contributors ranked by commit count
file.{{ ext }}@/git/NOTES.md                   # git notes (read + write)
file.{{ ext }}@/diff/HEAD.diff                 # uncommitted changes
file.{{ ext }}@/diff/<branch>.diff             # diff against any ref (lookup-only)
file.{{ ext }}@/history/                        # historical file versions
```

**Git companion files (symbol-level):**

```
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/LOG.md        # commits touching this symbol
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/BLAME.md      # per-line authorship for this symbol
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/history/       # historical versions of the containing file
```

### Symbol Naming

- Top-level symbols: `symbols/my_function.{{ ext }}`
- Trait/interface impls: `symbols/Display_for_Foo.{{ ext }}`
- Name collisions get `~Kind` suffixes: `symbols/Foo~Struct.{{ ext }}`, `symbols/Foo~Impl.{{ ext }}`
- Methods nest: `symbols/Foo~Impl@/new.{{ ext }}`

**Always read `OVERVIEW.md` first** to discover exact symbol names.

### Editing

| Task | How |
|-|-|
| Rewrite a function | Write to `symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Edit within a function | Use find-and-replace on `symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Change imports | Edit `symbols/imports.{{ ext }}` |
| Add content after a symbol | Append to `symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Change a signature | Write to `symbols/Foo@/signature.{{ ext }}` |
| Clear a docstring | Truncate `symbols/Foo@/docstring.txt` |
| Rename a symbol (project-wide) | `mv symbols/Foo@/ symbols/Bar@/` |
| Delete a symbol | `rmdir symbols/Foo@/` |
| Delete a line range | `rm file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20` |
| Apply a code action | `patch -p1 < symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff` |

All writes are **validated by tree-sitter** and **auto-formatted** before being spliced back.

> Writes re-parse the file — symbol names may change afterward (disambiguators added/removed,
> symbols deleted). Re-read `OVERVIEW.md` before accessing other symbols in the same file.

### Repository Level

```
@/git/STATUS.md                              # working tree status
@/git/branches/                              # local branches (mv = git branch -m)
@/git/tags/                                  # tag listing
@/STATUS.md                                  # mount status
@/GUIDE.md                                   # this guide
```

### Error Codes

| Error | Meaning | Action |
|-|-|-|
| `EINVAL` | Invalid input | Fix content: bad syntax, invalid UTF-8, stale target |
| `ENOTSUP` | Not supported | No decomposer for this language. Edit source directly |
| `EIO` | System failure | Retry once; if persistent, report |
| `EACCES` | Permission denied | File is read-only |
| `ENOENT` | Not found | Re-read `OVERVIEW.md` or `ls symbols/` — the name may have changed after a write |
